</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Allegations of harassment, arbitrary detention and excessive use of force against 
activists and peaceful protesters in the context of the parliamentary elections held on 
4 December 2011. According to the information received: on 5 December 2011, 
approximately 5,000 to 10,000 demonstrators gathered at the Chistye Prudy area in 
Moscow to express dissent against the reportedly fraudulent parliamentary election 
results. Law enforcement officials reportedly resorted to excessive use of force to 
disperse the assembly; with the detention of nearly 900 protesters between 5 and 6 
December. More detentions were also reported in other cities, including 
approximately 200 persons in Saint Petersburg. Human rights organizations, 
including the independent election monitoring group &#8220;Golos&#8221; and other human rights 
defenders, were allegedly subjected to threats, harassment and intimidation in the run 
up to the parliamentary elections and its aftermath.  
