<p>Allegations of surveillance and intimidation, arbitrary arrest and detention and 
unlawful raids. According to the information received, on 15 November 2011, Ms. 
Jestina Mukoko was followed around greater Harare by an unidentified man driving a 
car of a type which may be owned by, or associated with, State agents. The 
intimidation of Ms. Mukoko may form part of a pattern of harassment against human 
rights defenders in Zimbabwe in the context of the forthcoming elections. Ms. 
Mukoko may be at risk of enforced disappearance. Mr. Fadzai December and Ms. 
Molly Chimhanda, project officers of the Media Monitoring Project of Zimbabwe 
(MMPZ) and Mr. Gilbert Mabusa, member of the MMPZ are reportedly in detention 
at Gwanda Remand Prison as a consequence of their activities in the promotion and 
protection of human rights, namely the right to freedom of opinion and expression. 
Their charges are reportedly linked to a workshop organized by the MMPZ on 24 
November 2011. Reportedly, Harare police officers raided the MMPZ premises, 
confiscated materials belonging to the organization and arrested MMPZ Project 
Coordinator Mr. Andrew Moyse. 
