Reportedly, the perpetrators approached him in the area of Ghundai near Jamrod 
Bazaar, Khyber Agency. Before his death he had been working with a number of 
peace groups in campaigning for the release of dozens of prisoners under the 
Frontiers Crimes Regulations and was involved in organizing a congregation of tribal 
elders to campaign against terrorism. He had allegedly received death threats in the 
past from local militants. He is the third member of HRCP to be killed this year, 
following the killing of Mr. Siddique Eido, journalist and HRCP member, in 
Balochistan and Mr Naeem Sabir, HRCP Coordinator in Khudzar district, 
Balochistan ( see A/HRC/18/51 case no . PAK 17/2010).   
</p>
<p> </p>

