official Independence Day organized by the local authorities. Allegedly, 20 to 30 
unidentified persons in OzenMunaiGaz Company uniforms went to the stage 
constructed for the Independence Day event and began destroying sound equipment. 
Violent clashes occurred between protesters and the police. The law enforcement 
were allegedly allowed to use live rounds against protesters. On 17 December, a State 
of Emergency was declared in the town of Zhanaozen, which was extended until 31 
January 2012. 
