<p><b>Trafficking;   
</b></p>
<p> 
Alleged trafficking of persons, often migrants and refugees from Sudan, for the 
purpose of organ removal in Egypt. According to information received, an increasing 
number of Sudanese refugees and asylum seekers are trafficked to Egypt for the 
removal of their kidneys. The victims include children and women, many of them 
from Darfur, who have fled the conflict to seek asylum in Egypt. Victims are often 
deceived into giving their consent to sell their organs, or in other cases are completely 
unaware that their organ was being removed.  Victims suffer health consequences and 
social stigmatization as a result. 
