</p>
<p><b>Independence of 
</b></p>
<p><b>judges and lawyers;   
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Alleged due process violations. According to the new information received, five 
habeas corpus petitions were filed on behalf of Messrs. Antonio Guerrero Rodriguez, 
Fernando Gonz&#225;lez Llort, Gerardo Hern&#225;ndez Nordelo, Ram&#243;n Labanino Salazar and 
Ren&#233; Gonz&#225;lez Sehwerert. It is alleged that the same judge previously in charge of 
these cases, Ms. Joan A. Lenart of Florida South District, has been assigned to decide 
on the habeas corpus procedures. In addition, only part of the evidence available in 
these cases was allegedly disclosed, potentially affecting the effective right to defence 
of the defendants, including access to all material which could be exculpatory. These 
individuals were the subject of earlier communications (see A/HRC/11/41/Add.1, 
paras. 332 ff.). 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
