<p>Court order allegedly imposing ban on entering Kuala Lumpur. According to the 
information received, on 7 July 2011, the Magistrate&#8223;s Court in Kuala Lumpur issued a 
restriction order prohibiting a total of 91 individuals, including Mr. Yap Swee Seng, 
Mr. Ong Boon Keong, Ms. Enalini A/P Elumalai, Mr. Zaid bin Kamuruddin, Mr. Syed 
Shahir, Mr. Wong Chin Huat, Mr. Syed Ibrahim, Mr. Haris Ibrahim, Ms. Fadiah 
Nadwa, Mr. Kohila A/P Yanasekaran, Mr. Muhammad Hilma Idham, Mr. Mohd Shukri 
Che Ab Razab and Mr. Arutchelvan A/L Subramaniam (see previous communication 
above case no. MYS 6/2011), from remaining in, entering or passing through Kuala 
Lumpur. The ban can reportedly remain in place for up to seven days and a breach of 
the ban can result in a fine and /or imprisoned for up to six months.  It is alleged that 
the Court issued the order amid preparations for a &#180;Walk for Democracy&#180; demonstration 
organized by Bersih, which took place on 9 July 2011. More than a hundred activists 
were reportedly arrested after their participation in supporting the demonstration. 
</p>
